<br>
Epic:<br>
-Lowest of the three DPS but only by a slim margin, but equal to air against the larvae (lowest level mobs we fought).<br>
-Druid had to cast tunare's the fewest times per hour.<br>
-Tinku's nuke dps was better as she saved mana not having to cast DS.<br>
<br>
61 air:<br>
-Higher DPS than epic (very slight), lower than water (even when front tanking) <br>
-Druid had to heal 1.6 times more often than epic.<br>
-I haven't scanned the log yet to compair melee hits vs. when proc hit mob, but druid things pets proc must be doing damage only and ignoring the stun portion considering the amount proc hit vs. how fast the pet got hit.<br>
<br>
62 water:<br>
-Highest DPS, lotta proc.  Could not keep agro off him even with long head start by DC pets, so no BS other than when running away or when we had some fun with agro kiting <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
-Druid hated this pet with a passion and droped to zero nukes 100% healing and still needed med time.<br>
<br>
Synopsis:<br>
Epic still the best pet for our group, our DPS was higher as druid/mage could nuke more.<br>
<br>
Water best pet when tank joins us, or on raid.<br>
<br>
I guess air pet for use against casters? does the stun portion acctually hold?  Like you see the message when clerics cast stun spells with DD component and land them without the  stun portion taking effect on 55+ mobs, is it the same with air pet?<br>
<br>
My test didn't address the caster question, gonna try him against some lvl 60 druid trees in PoS I guess. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Mistress Bellia Divinewind <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bcodeofsilence98698">&lt;Code of Silence&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Tinku's lvl 62 Phantasmist Pet<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231078">I am ghetto</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kathodos>Kathodos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 369<br> <font color=#333333>(2/3/03 4:41:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/war3/images/human/units/portraits/waterelement.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet tank for group</span><hr size=1> Air Pet's stun will work on any mob that isn't immune to stuns.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=1020&amp;source=Live" target="top">AirElementalStrike</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
1:  Stun(3.0 sec/6000)<br>
2:  Decrease Hitpoints by 11 (L1) to 75 (L65)<br>
<br>
So unless the mob is immune to stuns, resists the proc 100%, or is higher than level 6000, the stun will land.<br>
<br>
And for reference, the epic pet's cast stun is as follows:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=848&amp;source=Live" target="top">ElementalMasteryStrike</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
1:  Stun(3.0 sec/6000)<br>
2:  Decrease Hitpoints by 36 (L1) to 100 (L65)<br>
<br>
So same rules apply, but due to level 49 cap (50 with focus), it's much more likely to get a 100% resist. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365" target="top">Kathodos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=279732" target="top">Kantreach</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Tholuxe Paells</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kathodos>Kathodos</A> at: 2/3/03 4:44:06 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bellia>Bellia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#333333>(2/6/03 10:24:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=964.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.belliapics.homestead.com/files/bellia.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet tank for group</span><hr size=1> Well, I stand corrected, Air pet was god-like for us in BoT for the last three days.  No gater, no CHs, more casters being interupted then I've seen in a LONG time.  And he is a MUCH better tank against the lvl 63-64 militis mobs, still won't survive more than 10 seconds without a heal on unslowed mobs but neither will my SK buddy in there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
